Citation.sAbstract: A visual and volume-variable high-pressure phase equilibrium analyzer (PEA) was used for measuring the  isothermal vapor-liquid equilibrium (VLE) phase boundaries of CO2 + ethanol and CO2 + acetone at  temperatures from (291.15 to 313.15) K over a wide composition range. The isothermal phase equilibrium  properties obtained from this work were compared with literature values to clarify the inconsistency of the  VLE data taken from different sources. The new VLE data were correlated with the Soave-Redlich-Kwong,  the Peng-Robinson, and the Patel-Teja equations of state incorporating with the one-parameter and the  two-parameter van der Waals one-fluid mixing rules, respectively.
Citation.sTitle: Vapor-Liquid Phase Boundaries of Binary Mixtures of Carbon Dioxide with Ethanol and Acetone
